    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_alǧac" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>alǧac</orth><form type="variant"
                            ><orth>alǧaw</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>alǧawinʒæ</orth><form
                        type="variant"><orth>ʒalǧawinʒæ</orth></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>сковородка с ручкой</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>frying pan with a handle</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ciwanæj ʒalǧawinʒitæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>чугунные сковороды</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>cast iron griddles</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"
                            /><biblScope>245%l3%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>xastoj wærdættæm... ajdæntæ, ḱyryntæ, bandættæ, agtæ, alǧactæ,
                            tæbæǧtæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>несли на арбы зеркала, сундуки, стулья, котлы, сковороды, тарелки</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>mirrors, chests, chairs, cauldrons, griddles, plates were carried on
                                carts</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"
                            /><biblScope>166—167</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Сопоставляется с <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>jalǧauč</w>
                        <gloss><q>сковородка с ручкой</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>alγaj</w>
                        <gloss><q>плоская кастрюля</q></gloss></mentioned>; по-видимому, образовано
                    от глагола %iyalǧa%i-, %iǰalǧa%i- ‘скреплять’, ‘прикреплять’ (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>III 174, IV
                        39</biblScope></bibl>) со значением ‘(сковорода) с прикрепленной, припаянной
                    (ручкой)’. Колебание начального элемента в осетинском (%ialǧ-ʒalǧ%i-) отражало
                    бы в этом случае чередование %iу%i и %iǰ%i в тюркских наречиях (%iyalǧ%i- ||
                    %iǰalǧ%i-) Дигорское окончание -%iwinʒæ%i могло быть результатом семантической
                    контаминации с глаголом %iawinʒun%i ‘подвешивать’ [см. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_awynʒyn"/>] („сковорода, которую можно подвешивать“). Сюда же
                    примыкают <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>jalghu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"
                        ><w>jälgha</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>joalghu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="agx"><lang/>
                        <w>jaglaw</w>
                        <gloss><q>сковородка с ручкой</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It is compared with <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>jalǧauč</w>
                        <gloss><q>griddle</q></gloss></mentioned>; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>alγaj</w>
                        <gloss><q>flat pot</q></gloss></mentioned>; it is apparently derived from
                    the verb %iyalǧa%i-, %iǰalǧa%i- ‘put together’, ‘attach’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>III 174, IV 39</biblScope></bibl>) with
                    the meaning ‘(pan) with attached, brazed (handle)’. Variation of the initial
                    element in Ossetic (%ialǧ-ʒalǧ%i-) would reflect in this case alternation
                    between %iу%i and %iǰ%i in Turkic dialects (%iyalǧ%i- || %iǰalǧ%i-) Digor ending
                    -%iwinʒæ%i could be a result of semantic contamination with the verb %iawinʒun%i
                    ‘hang’ [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_awynʒyn"/>] (“a pan that can be
                    hung”). Also here <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>jalghu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"
                        ><w>jälgha</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>joalghu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="agx"><lang/>
                        <w>jaglaw</w>
                        <gloss><q>griddle</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
            </entry>
